Mojo's Python virtual environment created at /home/codespace/.modular/pkg/packages.modular.com_mojo/venv

If you are using ZSH (default on macOS), run the following commands:

echo 'export MODULAR_HOME="/home/codespace/.modular"' >> ~/.zshrc
echo 'export PATH="/home/codespace/.modular/pkg/packages.modular.com_mojo/bin:$PATH"' >> ~/.zshrc
source ~/.zshrc

If you are using bash, run the following commands:

BASHRC=$( [ -f "$HOME/.bash_profile" ] && echo "$HOME/.bash_profile" || echo "$HOME/.bashrc" )
echo 'export MODULAR_HOME="/home/codespace/.modular"' >> "$BASHRC"
echo 'export PATH="/home/codespace/.modular/pkg/packages.modular.com_mojo/bin:$PATH"' >> "$BASHRC"
source "$BASHRC"

Then enter 'mojo' to start the Mojo REPL.

For tool help, enter 'mojo --help'.
For more docs, see https://docs.modular.com/mojo.